0 \leqslant x < 1
\sum_{j=0}^\infty x^j = \frac{1}{1-x},
\sum_{j=0}^h j\cdot x^{j-1} \leqslant \sum_{j=0}^\infty j\cdot x^{j-1} = \frac{1}{(1-x)^2}.
